  "texts": [
    "They find that ChatGPT performs better when you make the task at hand very clear by stating that you are expecting it to serve as an MT system in a particular domain.",
    "The temperature, a (hyper)parameter that can be set to control the level of randomness/unpredictibility in the texts it generates, has a relatively small impact when dealing with highresource languages (i.e.",
    "languages for which we generally have a large amount of linguistic resources, e.g.",
    "German or French).",
    "Additionally, they conduct a 'chain of thought' experiment where ChatGPT is prompted to not only translate but also explain its 'thoughts' while doing so."
  ],
